==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: natural gas
<hw>natural gas</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The combustible gas found
associated with petroleum deposits, and also in other geological
formations, comprised predominantly of methane plus variable other
constituents. It is an important source of energy, and is transported
long distances by pipelines, or in a liquefied state in tankers, for
commercial distribution. Some natural gas deposits contain helium, and
comprise the primary source of that rare element.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> gas.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Naturalism</ent>⟦br⟧
